{"title_page": "Bored Shorts TV", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name            = Bored Shorts TV\n| image           = Bored Shorts TV logo.jpg\n| caption         = \n| birth_name      = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date      = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{birth-date and age|birth date\u2020}} -->\n| birth_place     =\n| death_date      = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{death-date and age|death date\u2020|birth date\u2020}} -->\n| death_place     = \n| nationality     = \n| occupation      = \n| website         = {{url|http://boredshorts.tv}}\n| pseudonym       = <!-- use for individuals only -->\n| channel_name    = Bored Shorts TV<!-- use for channels only -->\n| years_active    = <!-- year of channel's creation until its discontinuation or present day -->\n| genre           = [[Entertainment]]\n| subscribers     = \n| subscriber_date = <!-- date at which the given number of subscribers is correct -->\n| views           = \n| view_date       = <!-- date at which the given number of views is correct -->\n| network         = <!-- multi-channel network (MCN) to which the channel has signed (past and/or present), if any -->\n| associated_acts = Richard Sharrah \n| silver_button   = <!-- yes/no; only use if the individual/channel has been awarded with a silver play button by YouTube -->\n| silver_year     = <!-- year in which the channel reached 100,000 subscribers -->\n| gold_button     = <!-- yes/no; only use if the individual/channel has been awarded with a gold play button by YouTube -->\n| gold_year       = <!-- year in which the channel reached 1,000,000 subscribers -->\n| stats_update    = <!-- date at which given channel statistics are correct -->\n}}\n\n'''Bored Shorts TV''' is a [[YouTube]] channel created by brothers Brett, David, John, and Randy Roberts and friend Richard Sharrah and launched on YouTube on March 3, 2011. Bored Shorts TV publish the video series Kid History, Kid Snippets, Autocorrect Awareness, and others. The channel has 494,000 subscribers and over 200 million upload views as of August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=BoredShortsTV|work=[[YouTube]]|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/BoredShortsTV|accessdate=29 April 2015}}</ref> The channel is best known for its Kid History series where each episode has a group of children tell a true story from the Roberts brothers' lives.  The stories are acted out by the brothers using the voices of the children.<ref name=DNews1>{{cite news|last=Toone|first=Trent|title=Hilarious Mormon YouTube series all about family|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/705388413/Hilarious-Mormon-YouTube-series-all-about-family.html|accessdate=15 January 2014|newspaper=Deseret News|date=1 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe Roberts brothers grew up making home videos but Kid History\u2014the flagship series on BoredShortsTV\u2014was not created until after their success in a video competition.<ref>{{cite news|last=Petersen|first=Sarah|title=1 videos from YouTube stars with Utah ties|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/top/1393/10/Bored-Shorts-TV-Kid-History-11-videos-from-YouTube-stars-with-Utah-ties.html|accessdate=15 January 2014|newspaper=Deseret News|date=19 March 2013}}</ref>  Randy Roberts developed the concept\u2014a twist on another popular YouTube series \"Drunk History\"<ref name=SLTrib>{{cite news|last=Horiuchi|first=Vince|title=Utah brothers 'Kid History' a YouTube smash|url=http://www.sltrib.com/sltrib/entertainment/51854057-81/roberts-history-brothers-randy.html.csp|accessdate=15 January 2014|newspaper=The Salt Lake Tribune|date=2 June 2011}}</ref>\u2014and enlisted the help of his brothers to create the first episode to enter into the Lingos Film festival, a small [[Latter-day Saints|LDS]] film festival in [[New York City]], which it won gaining 80 percent of the votes.<ref name=DNews1 /><ref name=DailyUniverse>{{cite news|last=Saatkamp|first=Chelsey|title=The history behind Kid History|url=http://universe.byu.edu/2011/09/15/the-history-behind-kid-history/|accessdate=15 January 2014|newspaper=The Daily Universe|date=15 September 2011}}</ref><ref name=KSL>{{cite news|last=Rode|first=Rebecca|title=Have You Seen This? 'Kid History' brothers become Web celebrities |url=http://www.ksl.com/?sid=15418624|accessdate=15 January 2014|newspaper=KSL.com|date=7 May 2011}}</ref>   Kid History episodes feature several additional members of the Roberts extended family. Bored Shorts TV does all of its own media production out of their studio in [[Lindon, Utah|Orem, Utah]].<ref name=DNews1 />\n\nKid History was followed by other series including: Kid Snippets, Autocorrect Awareness, and Kid Movie Trailers.  A new video is produced every Monday.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kid Snippets: \"Catching Santa\" (Kids Tell, Adults Act)|url=http://news.msn.com/science-technology/video?videoid=b5636c41-ce7a-42cb-9823-0dc4068af6a4|publisher=MSN news|accessdate=15 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116131235/http://news.msn.com/science-technology/video?videoid=b5636c41-ce7a-42cb-9823-0dc4068af6a4|archive-date=January 16, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> There has been some interest in creating a show with the Kid History creator, and the Roberts brothers have been approached by several TV networks.<ref name=KSL /><ref name=UV360>{{cite news|title=Kid History In The Making|url=http://utahvalley360.com/2013/11/10/kid-history-in-the-making/|accessdate=15 January 2014|newspaper=Utah Valley 360|date=10 November 2013}}</ref>\n\nKid Snippets are videos that include adults, but the all the adults in the videos are voiced by two children, either male or female. The topic of Kid Snippets is what might happen if people grew up but their minds didn't develop as they mature. \n\nAfter almost a year's hiatus, BoredShorts returned with 2 new videos at the end of 2017.\n\nAfter almost another year\u2019s hiatus, BoredShorts returned again with a new snippet in September 2018.\n\n==CVX Live==\nIn 2015, the creators of Bored Shorts TV created a YouTube convention called [[CVX Live]]. The convention took place August 7\u20138 at Utah Valley University and featured 35 different YouTube celebrities with meet & greets, main stage performances, private meet-ups and other activities. Total attendance at the event was 6,112.<ref>{{cite news|last=KSL.com|first=Taylor, Amanda|title=UVU hosts YouTubers, fans at new convention|url=https://www.ksl.com/?sid=35880309&nid=148&title=uvu-hosts-youtubers-fans-at-new-convention|accessdate=August 9, 2015|work=KSL.com|date=August 9, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Deseret News|first=Petersen, Sarah|title=27 famous YouTubers with Utah connections share tips, love for videos|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/top/3342/0/27-famous-YouTubers-with-Utah-connections-share-tips-love-for-videos.html|accessdate=August 10, 2015|work=Deseret News|date=August 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=The Salt Lake Tribune|first=Means, Sean P|title=CVX Live, a fan convention for online video, debuting in Orem, August 7\u20138|url=http://www.sltrib.com/blogs/cricket/2538664-155/cvx-live-a-fan-convention-for|accessdate=May 21, 2015|work=The Salt Lake Tribune|date=May 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe first CVX Live was held on August 7\u20138, 2015 at the [[UCCU Center]] in [[Orem, Utah]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Daily Herald|first=Neely, Karissa|title=Fans and local celebrities join up at CVX Live event|url=http://www.heraldextra.com/news/local/fans-and-local-celebrities-join-up-at-cvx-live-event/article_4c54a16e-8059-51e5-abec-d069743e4ed0.html|accessdate=August 9, 2015|work=Daily Herald|date=August 9, 2015}}</ref> The event featured main stage performances and public meet and greets by YouTube creators.<ref>{{cite web|last=Means|first=Sean P.|url=http://www.sltrib.com/home/2787201-155/online-rock-stars-to-meet-their|title=Online 'rock stars' to meet their Utah fans at CVX Live|publisher=SLTRIB.com|date=August 2, 2015|accessdate=August 2, 2015}}</ref> The event included the introduction of  [[The Next Big YouTuber]] contest.<ref>{{cite web|last=Miller|first=Christensen, Megan|url=http://www.ksl.com/?sid=35793169&nid=148&s_cid=rss-extlink|title=Tween YouTuber a finalist in convention contest|publisher=KSL.com|date=August 3, 2015|accessdate=August 3, 2015}}</ref> The winner of this contest was Madilyn Paige<ref>{{cite web|last=Christensen|first=Megan Marsden, Megan|url=http://www.ksl.com/index.php?sid=35950829&nid=148&title=previous-voice-finalist-wins-local-next-big-youtuber|title=Previous 'Voice' finalist wins local 'Next Big YouTuber'|publisher=KSL.com|date=August 13, 2015|accessdate=August 13, 2015}}</ref> who was previously a finalist on ''[[The Voice (TV series)|The Voice]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Official website|1=http://boredshorts.tv/}}\n*{{YouTube|u=BoredShortsTV|{{PAGENAMEBASE}}}}\n*[https://www.facebook.com/kidhistory Facebook page]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140517205835/http://kidhistoryfoundation.org/ Kid History Foundation]\n\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2011]]\n[[Category:Entertainment-related YouTube channels]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name            = Bored Shorts TV\n| image           = Bored Shorts TV logo.jpg\n| caption         = \n| birth_name      = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date      = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{birth-date and age|birth date\u2020}} -->\n| birth_place     =\n| death_date      = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{death-date and age|death date\u2020|birth date\u2020}} -->\n| death_place     = \n| nationality     = \n| occupation      = \n| website         = {{url|http://boredshorts.tv}}\n| pseudonym       = <!-- use for individuals only -->\n| channel_name    = Bored Shorts TV<!-- use for channels only -->\n| years_active    = <!-- year of channel's creation until its discontinuation or pre